      <title>Postcard from Leopold Godowsky to Gottfried Galston, May 30, 1908</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>A postcard sent to Galston while he lived in Berlin from pianist Leopold Godowsky. The postcard is from Galston's own stationery, with his name and address printed on it. The note was glued to an interleaving page in the Chopin section of the Studienbuch, and concerns Godowsky's own interpretation of Chopin's Ã©tudes. The postmark date is May 30, 1908.</abstract>
